d-source> to health due to added fat and factors related to processing. Bak=
ed potatoes in their peels are likely the healthiest option.</p></div><div>=
<p>Other nutrient-dense options include whole eggs and fatty fish.</p></div=
><div><h3>What is the number 1 healthiest food in the world?</h3></div><div=
><p>It is not possible to identify a single healthiest food, but the health=
iest diet contains a variety of fresh, plant-based foods, lean protein, and=
 a range of nutrients.</p></div><div><h3>What are some of the most nutritio=
us foods?</h3></div><div><p>Oily fish, eggs, avocados, potatoes, and green =
leafy vegetables are some of the most nutritious foods.</p></div><div><p>Ho=
wever, no food provides all the nutrients we need, so it=E2=80=99s essentia=
l to have a varied diet that includes plenty of fresh ingredients and is as=
 little processed as possible. </p></div><div><p>The more processed a food =
is, the more likely nutrients are to be destroyed and unwanted nutrients, s=
uch as sugar or <a href=3D"https://www.healthline.com/nutrition/artificial-=
food" class=3D"content-link css-1c2ok3c">additives</a>, to be added. </p></=
div><div><h3>What is one food you can survive on?</h3></div><div><p>It is u=
nlikely that a person could survive for long on a single food source. Still=
